The paper presents an algorithm for machine learning that involves regularization and kernel functions. This suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories within computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and statistics (cs.ST). Given that the paper focuses on improving classification performance through regularization and kernel functions, it is most likely to belong to cs.LG, followed by cs.AI and cs.CV. The use of sparse solutions also suggests a potential connection to cs.DS. The paper may also touch on statistical concepts, hence cs.ST is also a possible sub-category.
